JOHANNESBURG – The Constitutional Court on Monday released a report into Bathabile Dlamini's conduct in the social grants crisis. Retired judge Bernard Ngoepe submitted the findings of the report into the former Social Development minister on 4 April. READ: Shabangu vows not to extend Sassa CPS contract The judge is highly critical of Dlamini’s testimony, saying she evaded some questions and avoided answering others. READ: Dlamini contradicts herself under oath She also answered some questions with other questions. In August, the Constitutional Court called for the inquiry, which then took place in January. It followed the South African Social Security Agency’s failure to meet a court deadline over social grant payments. eNCA